title: For Sale:  Surgeon 1086/R Long Action for .300 Win Mag calibers
postcontent:
These actions are the absolute best on the market and almost impossible to find. If you are building a .300, this is what you want. This particular one comes with the .550" (300 Win Mag / 300 RUM etc) bolt face.

All 1086 actions come with a integral .250” recoil lug and 20 MOA 1913 picatinny rail that runs the full length of the action, as well as a side mounted bolt stop that is shrouded to help prevent accidental releasing of the bolt.

In the middle of the left bolt raceway is an anti-jam rail, the purpose of this rail is to prevent a round from lodging in the raceway when single loading the rifle through the ejection/loading port.

The raceway on the right hand side has an anti-bind rail just below the ejection/loading port, the purpose of this rail is to insure smooth bolt operation as the locking lug passes through the loading port.

The 1086 will work in conjunction with any stocks made for the Remington 700 long action with little to no modification as well as triggers and feeding systems.

title: For Sale:  Remington Sportsman 78 .30-06
postcontent:
I have a Remington Sportsman model 78 lightweight chambered in .30-06 for sale.  Apparently this thing is sort of a rare bird.  Remington only made the model 78 for 5-6 years and I dont see the lightweight version available at all.

I purchased this rifle in Oregon in 1988 simply because the stock stood out a little bit and I couldn't afford the fancier models.  This was my very first big game rifle I ever bought with my own money at the age of 13.

The rifle is in excellent condition for its age.  I've always carried it with the gun chap on it so there's no nicks or dings like you normally see on used guns of this age.  It's also a real tack driver with my handloads.  Sub 1" groups at 200 yards are possible if I'm shooting good.

I have shortened the length of pull 1/2" by cutting 2" off the stock and adding a Pachmayr recoil pad.  The stock is hollow based to reduce weight.  The action is blueprinted, the trigger is set to 2 pounds and is tuned very crisp.  

The rifle comes with a new Leupold 4-12X40mm scope, weaver rings and bases, a leather sling, and the gun chap.

I haven't carried this rifle in the field in the last six or seven years due to the old scope losing it's nitrogen and having plenty of other rifles ready to go.  I put the new scope on it but this rifle is still the odd man out.  It might have been my first big game rifle but the last few are what floats my boat.

Better to let it go to someone that can appreciate it than let it sit in my closet collecting dust.  I think $300 is a fair price to ask.  It's a bit more than I paid for the gun new but there's over $300 in accessories on it.  

Call Brian at REDACTED with any questions.

The 92 series of semiautomatic pistols operates on a short recoil, delayed blowback system, which yields; faster cycle times, exceptional accuracy and greater reliability. title: For Sale:  1952 Russian made sks
postcontent:
I have a 1952 Russian made sks for sale.

It's in almost new condition as it was reconditioned with the lamate stock before being surplused out.  All the numbers match and it would likely start to have some collectable value in time.

Here's the deal.  This gun is heavily modified.  I did it because I could and quite frankly the stock gun couldn't hit the broadside of a barn if you were inside of it!  LOL  Actually I've shot a few sks's and it was about on par with the rest of them.  

The action is glass bedded to the stock and is rock solid.  One can still remove the stock but it takes a bit of effort/prying to do so.  The action has been blueprinted and is very smooth.  The trigger is heavily modified to reduce triggerpull and creep.  A bit of grinding and welding involved with different springs.

This rifle holds inside 2.5" at 100 yards so it's fairly accurate now.  I put about a thousand rounds through it then tossed it into the closet where it collects dust.  This gun just isn't for me.

Shame I modified an early Russian SKS so if your a collector this one probably isn't for you.  If you just want a gun that goes BANG everytime you pull the trigger and is extremely accurate, for an sks that is, then this is a killer deal.

Contact Brian at REDACTED with any questions.

title: For Sale:  Stringer Federal Spike Strip System (NEW)
postcontent:
The STINGER system employs high strength, hollow steel spikes that penetrate all types of tires – including self-sealing and run-flats – and deflate them in a regulated manner. This prevents blowouts, slows the perpetrator’s vehicle to a safer rate of speed, and allows him to make a controlled stop. And STINGER spikes are effective on all types of vehicles, including cars, trucks, and buses.

Rock and Tilt Mechanism
The STINGER SPIKE SYSTEM uses patented technology to ensure effective tire penetration. A typical chase intervention flattens one to four tires, safely slowing and stopping the vehicle in just minutes. At the initial contact, the assembly automatically rocks toward the tire, pointing the spikes directly at the tread, allowing the full length of the spike to be used for penetration. And as the spikes pivot into the tire, the safety tip guards are pushed down. 

The assembly continues to rotate with the motion of the vehicle, driving the spikes deeply into the tire. The hollow spikes control the tire deflation rate, preventing a blowout and sudden loss of control.

The rolling tire then tilts the spike system in the opposite direction, allowing the spikes to pull completely out of the assembly. With the next rotation they are pushed fully into the tire – leaving no debris on the roadway. A tire typically picks up 4-6 spikes and deflates in 12-20 seconds.

Safe and Easy to Use

The STINGER device is designed for quick, reliable operation. A simple pull on the handle or a toss is all it takes to position the spikes. The single, accordion-action element deploys almost instantly, giving officers time to take cover. Extra-width road coverage and low visibility minimize avoidance by fleeing suspects. And, after spiking, a simple yank on the handle quickly retracts the unit, clearing the road for pursuit vehicles and other traffic.

STINGER Models
All STINGER models incorporate a reusable modular base, with molded sections built of high-strength, resilient synthetic polymer, which stands up to hard use under the harshest conditions. The base is designed to endure numerous pursuits and has withstood impacts in excess of 130mph. If, however, a unit is damaged, the individual sections are easily replaceable. title: For Sale:  Remington 597 Sporter Stainless .22LR
postcontent:
I hate to sell this rifle, but I am days away from a paycheck and I need food money to get me through.

It is a Remington model 597 Sporter Stainless in .22LR.  There is a cheap 4 power scope installed, and will be included.  It's not much of a scope but it is perfect for a .22, and has held zero for many shots.

It has a 20 inch barrel, and while it isn't the bull barrel, it is still a very heavy barrel.  

I have read a lot of complaints about the magazines jamming in this model, but the only problem I have ever had with the magazine is the catch/release mechanism inside the action.  There was a pin that kept coming loose inside that when loose, the firearm wouldn't hold a magazine in place.

I developed a fix by installing an extra take-down pin that holds the pin in place, and now that it can NOT come loose, it has not failed once.  The magazine feels like a center-fire rifle when you install or pop one out of the rifle.

I have the stock plastic magazine, as well as 2 metal magazines from www.keepshooting.com.  All of the magazines are listed as 10 round mags, but the 2 from keepshooting really only hold 9 each.

Sorry, but I don't have any airtime on my phone right now, so e-mail is the only way to get a hold of me.  If you don't want to wait for me to check e-mail, go ahead and call my phone 3 times in a row.  I won't be able to answer, but that will tell me I need to check e-mail and get back with you asap.  REDACTED  Please allow 15 to 20 minutes at least for me to get back with you, as I have to leave the house to use internet.

I also have the key that can lock the trigger, as well as the manual for the scope.  $150 Firm.  If you need me to sweeten the pot, I will throw in a little bit of ammo, (I don't have that much to give away, but it would be enough to test it out and get a little bit of practice.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Zastava M59/66 SKS
postcontent:
Rifle is in great shape and costs about half as much to run as an AR.  During the recent gun crisis I was always able to find ammo and it is still more available and cheaper than 223/556.  Plus it is powerful enough to hunt deer out to 150 yds or so. 
This platform is cheaper than anything comparable and there are a multitude of affordable modifications and accessories available - detachable mags(conversion takes less than 5 minutes) to very cool bullpup conversions (I just ordered one from Shernic Gunworks - checkit out on youtube - pretty awesome). These are very fun guns to own and in my opinion they are superior to the more popular AKs. - the AK is stamped out of sheet metal where these are milled and much sturdier construction.  The SKS also has a 20' barrel - is inherently more accurate and gives the bulet more velocity than the 16" AK.  If you want something short like the AK drop it into a bullpup stock and you've got a $1,000 gun!  
I bought several the day after Sandy Hook from www.samcoglobal.com and just don't need multiples.  So I'm looking for cash or trades to enhance my vintage gun collection.
